# Plan: Overload `--period` with absolute date range support

## Summary

Extend the existing `--period` flag across all 7 commands to accept absolute date ranges using `..` syntax, in addition to existing relative durations. Follows `gh` CLI conventions (`--created "2023-01-01..2023-06-01"`).

### Supported formats

| Syntax | Meaning | API params |
|--------|---------|------------|
| `7d`, `24h`, `1h` | Relative duration (existing) | `statsPeriod=7d` |
| `2024-01-01..2024-02-01` | Full range | `start=...&end=...` |
| `2024-01-01..` | Start only (open end) | `start=...` |
| `..2024-02-01` | End only (open start) | `end=...` |
| `>2024-01-01` | After date (exclusive) | `start=2024-01-02T00:00:00.000Z` |
| `>=2024-01-01` | From date (inclusive) | `start=2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z` |
| `<2024-02-01` | Before date (exclusive) | `end=2024-01-31T23:59:59.999Z` |
| `<=2024-02-01` | Through date (inclusive) | `end=2024-02-01T23:59:59.999Z` |

Date formats: `YYYY-MM-DD`, `YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS`, `YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ`, `YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS+HH:MM`

This matches the `gh` CLI operator syntax (e.g., `gh search issues --created ">2023-01-01"`).

