- Operator date-only normalization (tests mock timezone to a fixed offset for determinism):
  - `>=2024-01-01` → start has local midnight with local TZ offset
  - `>2024-01-01` → start has next day local midnight with local TZ offset
  - `<=2024-02-01` → end has local EOD with local TZ offset
  - `<2024-02-01` → end has prev day local EOD with local TZ offset
- Operator datetime passthrough (no day shift for precise times):
  - `>2024-01-01T12:00:00Z` → start `2024-01-01T12:00:00Z` (as-is)
- Timezone handling:
  - Date-only → local timezone offset applied (not UTC)
  - Datetime with explicit TZ → passed through as-is
  - Datetime without TZ → local timezone offset applied
- Backward compatibility: all existing relative values work (`"1h"`, `"24h"`, `"7d"`, `"14d"`, `"30d"`, `"90d"`)
- API params output for each format (relative, range, open-ended, all 4 operators)
- `timeRangeToSeconds` for relative, absolute, and open-ended

