## Edge cases

| Input | Behavior |
|-------|----------|
| `"7d..14d"` | Split on `..`, try to parse `"7d"` as date → `ValidationError("Invalid start date")` |
| `"2024-01-01"` (no `..`, no operator) | Fails relative regex, no `..`, no operator → `ValidationError("Use a duration (7d), range (2024-01-01..2024-02-01), or operator (>=2024-01-01)")` |
| `".."` | Both sides empty → `ValidationError` |
| `">"` / `">="` / `"<"` / `"<="` | Operator with no date → `ValidationError` |
| `"2024-01-01..2023-01-01"` | End before start → `ValidationError` |
| `"2030-01-01..2030-02-01"` | Future dates → valid (API returns empty results) |
| `">2024-01-01"` vs `">=2024-01-01"` | Different: `>` starts at next day, `>=` starts at same day midnight |
| `"<2024-02-01"` vs `"<=2024-02-01"` | Different: `<` ends at prev day EOD, `<=` ends at same day EOD |
| `">2024-01-01T12:00:00Z"` | Datetime with `>`: passed through as-is (already precise, no day adjustment) |
| `--follow --period "..2024-06-01"` | End-bounded + follow → `ValidationError("--follow cannot be used with an end date boundary")` |
| `--follow --period "<2024-06-01"` | Same — end-bounded + follow → `ValidationError` |

